Data Collection Method: NCDOT Count Assignments 13-07155 thru 13-07160 were counted over two days, with
one counter assigned to each zone (aka count assignment) of the US 421 (East Cornelius Boulevard) corridor.
Counters used Jamar count boards to count pedestrians crossing north to south and south to north US 421
within their zone. Each zone was marked in the field with a traffic cone. See the map attached on page 3 for the
complete study area map of the 6 zones counted.
